Reasoning: The paper deals with the verification of distributed systems, which involves the study of the behavior of concurrent processes. This makes it likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for sequentializing concurrent processes, which is related to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multiparty session types, which are a formalism for specifying communication protocols in distributed systems, making it relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the verification of properties related to communication and concurrency, which is related to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving the efficiency of verifying properties that require the consideration of concrete runs or values of variables, which is related to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
